CNCP v1 23324
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#11398: cannot call Set#intersection for set with Proxy ",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:29.469709+00:00",
  "text": "cannot call Set#intersection for set with Proxy \n\n### Vue version\n\nfd5c001\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a set with Proxy, such as `ref(new Set([...]))`\r\n2. Call `Set#intersection`\n\n### What is expected?\n\nIt shouldn't throw an error\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nIt throws error: \"Set operation called on non-Set object\"\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nVue: fd5c001\r\nTypeScript: 5.5.3\n```\n\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nThere is a workaround: `toRaw(mySet.value).intersection` does not throw error.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: reactivity",
    "has workaround",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
